The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 12 February is 214,828 (24,760.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 07 February, there were 9,229 new confirmed cases (1,063.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 31 January, there were 11,099 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 17% (1,870 fewer cases).
